node.text:
V-carving the #TTcherryCuttingBoard on the Stepcraft M.1000 CNC machine, available on our website, using the Amana Tool #45624-K 60° Spektra™ coated V-Groove bit from @toolstoday.
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Max depth of cut: .217"
- - - - - - -
This bit did a great job cutting cherry going mostly cross cutting, left a few fuzziest cleaned up with the @gatorfinishing micro zip with 220g, but zero chip out great to see! I then filled it with @totalboat epoxy with @blackdiamondpigments_com Bora Bora blue.
- - - - - - -

node.text:
What do you think the animal for letter V will be?  Cutting out one of the tiles in the #TTanimalAlphabet series using the Amana Tool #RC-45711 90° rotatable Insert carbide ‘V’-Groove In-Tech 11/16" diameter bit from @toolstoday on the Stepcraft M.1000 CNC machine using X-Fasten Double Sided tape item #WO-5BMC-7UO9, available on our website. Be sure to check out the plans for these tiles item no. ANIMAL__A_Z as well to make them yourself!
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 35ipm
Plunge Rate: 17.5ipm
Max Depth of Cut: .25"
- - - - - - -
Available on our website for just $26.14 the RC-45711 is an absolute steal! It makes a very clean cut through the stained pine with no cleanup work needed at all even on the tiny details
- - - - - - -

node.text:
My favorite method for filling small cracks and knots is Starbond Adhesives Black CA glue, item #K2, and the accelerator, item #A6, both available on our website! It is so quick and easy as the accelerator dries the glue within 30 seconds so you can get it sanded and move on with the project.  No waiting hours for epoxy to cure!
- -

Making the #TTnationalParkSign on the Stepcraft Q.408 4'x8' CNC machine, available on our website, using @corafoam_hdusigns 20lb HDU foam. **What do you think of how it turned out?
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
The plans for this project are available on our website item no. PARK_SIGN. I started off by applying some Oramask 813 to the prepainted piece.  I the carved into it using Amana Tool #RC-1102 90° Insert carbide ‘V’-Groove bit featuring 1-1/2" diameter, 3/4" cut height and 1/2” shank available from @toolstoday!
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Depth per pass: .5"
- - - - - - -
The bit cut insanely cleanly through the Oramask 813, also available on our website, and HDU foam leaving no cleanup work needed at all!  The piece was then painted with General Finishes Snow White milk paint, available on our website.
- - - - - - -
I then switched out for the Amana Tool #46202-K 1/4" Spektra™ coated downcut bit to do all of the clearing out on the flat bottom V-carve.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 120ipm
Plunge Rate: 60ipm
Depth per pass: .25"
- - - - - - -
I then switched out to the Amana Tool #RC-1148 60° insert carbide V-Groove bit to do all of the fine detail work for a nice clean cut!
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Max Depth: .25"
- - - - - - -
I then switched out for the #46315-K 1/4" Spektra™ coated upcut bit to do the profile cutting.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 120ipm
Plunge Rate: 60ipm
Depth per pass: .25"
- - - - - - -
The piece was taped off and painted and keyhol slots were made using the Amana Tool #45650 3/8" diameter keyhole bit.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 100ipm
Plunge Rate: 50ipm
Depth per pass: .325"
- - - - - - -
The piece was cut free at the bandsaw and flush trimmed with the Amana Tool #47092 1/4" diameter 1" cut height bit.  A chamfer was added on the back side with the Amana Tool #49400 45° 1-1/4" diameter chamfer bit.  The rest of the painting was completed and the piece was finished with Minwax Sparurethane in satin.
- - - - - - -

V-carving the #TTcherryCuttingBoard on the Stepcraft M.1000 CNC machine, available on our website, using the Amana Tool #45624-K 60° Spektra™ coated V-Groove bit from @toolstoday.
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Max depth of cut: .217"
- - - - - - -
This bit did a great job cutting cherry going mostly cross cutting, left a few fuzziest cleaned up with the @gatorfinishing micro zip with 220g, but zero chip out great to see! I then filled it with @totalboat epoxy with @blackdiamondpigments_com Bora Bora blue.
- - - - - - -

node.text:
V-carving a sign on the Stepcraft M.1000 CNC machine, available on our website, using the Amana Tool #RC-1141 Insert carbide 1" diameter 1/4" shank V-Groove bit from @toolstoday.
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 35ipm
Plunge Rate: 17.5ipm
Max depth per pass: .25"
- - - - - - -
This bit did a great job cutting through this plywood stained with General Finishes Spiced Walnut stain, available on our website.  It left a perfectly clean cut especially with the built in clean up pass in the Vectric V-carve pro software, available on our website!
- - - - - - -
